    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5 min <span class=\"text-danger\">[10 min] </span>to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with tin foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-fragrant-coconutty-pollock-curry/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Cut the <strong>lemongrass</strong> in half and the <strong>tomatoes</strong> into wedges, then add these to the dish</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-fragrant-coconutty-pollock-curry/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crush the <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife and remove the skins</p><p>Cut the<strong> ginger </strong>in half (no need to peel!)</p><p>Add the<strong> crushed garlic </strong>and<strong> halved ginger</strong> to the dish</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-fragrant-coconutty-pollock-curry/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse the<strong> brown rice </strong>under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> rinsed brown rice</strong>, <strong>curry powder </strong>and<strong> ground turmeric </strong>to the dish</p><p>Add in the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-fragrant-coconutty-pollock-curry/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> and 500ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [750] [1L]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> to the dish<strong> </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 20 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-fragrant-coconutty-pollock-curry/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-fragrant-coconutty-pollock-curry/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After 20 min, remove the dish from the oven and add the<strong> </strong>juice<strong> </strong>of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>diced pollock </strong>(unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!) and return the dish to the oven for 4-5 min or until the white fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> all-in-one fragrant coconutty pollock curry</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-fragrant-coconutty-pollock-curry/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, tear the<strong> coriander </strong>over the <strong>all-in-one</strong> <strong>fragrant coconutty pollock curry</strong></p><p>Garnish with a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch out for the ginger halves and lemongrass, discard them!</p><p>Let everyone dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
